Since everyone is posting about 2016, here’s mine. 2016 was a hard year, mom was diagnosed with MDS in april of that year. we had so much hope , I traveled with mom dad to Mumbai then to Houston looking for treatment options. We also celebrated mom’s last birthday on earth that year. 💔 

1️⃣ I attended my first ever food blogging conference in Salt Lake City. I do miss everything food conference.

2️⃣ Kept cooking at home a lot, making thalis which I rarely make now.

3️⃣ Celebrated what would be mom’s last birthday on earth in India.

4️⃣ Reached 5000 followers on Insta, those were the times of carousel pics only!

5️⃣ Set up our first home in US (we had only lived in rental apartments before that).

6️⃣ I published my very famous paan ladoo that year- that many of you still make every year for Diwali!

7️⃣ Coffee date with mom and dad in between all the doctor appointments and hospital visits.  

8️⃣ I learnt so much about blogging at this conference. I learnt that this could be my job and I made it happen! 

#2016

Dear Customers, as you may have heard – it is with great sadness to announce that after an excess of 20 years of serving our wonderful customers, we are now looking to retire and hope to find a lovely buyer for the shop. Thank you so so much to everyone who left some amazing comments on a few recent facebook posts, and thank you to all those who have been into the shop expressing their heartache of such news – it has truly been overwhelming and we can’t thank you all enough for all the love and support. Also, a BIG THANK YOU to those who have dropped off cards and flowers for Mum wishing her a speedy recovery – we are truly grateful.
Please note that the shop will NOT BE CLOSING but will be changing hands once there is a buyer. Rest assured, we will still be open as normal until that sad time comes and we will keep you up to date here. In the meantime, please feel free to pop in as often or as little as you wish… even if its to ask how we make the sauces… =P Big Love, All at Heaton Road Fish and Chips x

Mint Virgin Mojito! 🍹: a quick summer refresher to beat the heat!
➡️ 6-7 mint leaves + more to garnish
➡️ half lime, cut into quarters + more for serving 
➡️ 2 teaspoons sweetener of choice
➡️ ice cubes
➡️ 1 cup sparkling water (I used plain)

Add mint leaves and half of a lime (quartered) to your glass. Using a muddler press the leaves and the lime to release the juice and oils from the leaves. Leave it for 5 minutes. Then add the sweetener of choice (I used honey), crush again using a muddler. Add ice cubes and then top with 1 cup of sparkling water. Add a lime wedges and more mint leaves to garnish. This serves 1. Enjoy!

#summerdrinks #mocktails🍹

Easy Greek Yogurt Bagels- only 4 ingredients (including salt)! This is one viral recipe that you need to try! 😃.-1 cup bread flour-1 & 1/2 tsp baking powder -1/4 tsp salt-1 cup 0% greek yogurt.Mix flour, baking powder, and salt together in a large bowl. Add yogurt and mix with a fork initially until it all starts coming together. Then use your hands to bring the dough together. It will be sticky. Knead the dough for 2 mins using your hands. You can lightly grease your hands while kneading the dough but resist the temptation to add more flour. Divide into 4 parts. Roll each part into a rope and then bring the ends together to shape into a bagel. Place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper..Brush with egg wash (or milk), sprinkle everything bagel seasoning on top (optional) and then bake at 375 F for 25-30 minutes. Let cool for 20 minutes and then slice them. Enjoy !.

Pistachio Latte ☕️ because the weather calls for it! 🍁 This is an easy homemade version which can be modified to taste and preference. Use light roast and less coffee if you don’t prefer a strong cup of coffee. You can also use less milk as per your taste. I honestly think this coffee tastes best with oat milk! Recipe below 👇 
.
⭐️2-3 tbsp water
⭐️1 & 1/2 tsp coffee, I used Tasters choice instant coffee medium roast. Use less coffee and light roast if you prefer light coffee.
⭐️8 oz milk of choice, I used oat milk
⭐️1 tablespoon pistachio butter 
⭐️crushed pistachios, to sprinkle 
.
Add 2-3 tbsp water to a cup along with coffee. Microwave it until it becomes hot. Meanwhile heat up milk and pistachio butter. You can add sugar but I did not add any since pistachio butter was already sweetened. Whisk the coffee using a frother. Transfer over the warm milk. Garnish with chopped pistachios!
#coffee #fallvibes
